  "response": "A milkshake should not be left out of the fridge for more than **2 hours** at room temperature (up to 90\u00b0F or 32\u00b0C). If the temperature is above 90\u00b0F, the safe window shortens to **1 hour**. \n\nMilkshakes contain dairy products, such as milk and ice cream, which are highly perishable and can grow harmful bacteria like Salmonella or E. coli when left at room temperature for too long. For food safety, it's best to refrigerate your milkshake as soon as possible or consume it promptly after it's made. If it's left out longer than the recommended time, it's safer to discard it.",
